OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772041214
OL,3,CPeter Mandelson complains to
OL,4,Cjournalists about news coverage of his
OL,5,Carrest
OL,7,FLawyers acting on behalf of Mandelson
OL,8,Fmade an unusual statement on Tuesday
OL,9,Fin which they claimed his arrest was
OL,10,Fprompted by a "baseless suggestion"
OL,11,Fthat he was "planning to leave the
OL,12,Fcountry".
OL,14,FTwo plain clothed police officers
OL,15,Fentered Mandelson's North London home
OL,16,Fat 4.15pm on Monday. It was more than
OL,17,Fhalf an hour before the two officers
OL,18,Femerged wearing body cameras to escort
OL,19,FMandelson into an unmarked police car.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1772041214
OL,3,CPeter Mandelson complains to
OL,4,Cjournalists about news coverage of his
OL,5,Carrest
OL,7,FA spokesman for the law firm Mischon
OL,8,Fde Reya, on behalf of Mandelson, said:
OL,9,F"Peter Mandelson was arrested
OL,10,Fyesterday despite an agreement with
OL,11,Fthe police that he would attend an
OL,12,Finterview next month on a voluntary
OL,13,Fbasis.
OL,15,F"The arrest was prompted by a baseless
OL,16,Fsuggestion that he was planning to
OL,17,Fleave the country and take up
OL,18,Fpermanent residence abroad.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
